---
Configure tirith protection for an AI coding tool

Usage: tirith setup [OPTIONS] <TOOL>

Arguments:
  <TOOL>  Tool to configure: claude-code, codex, cursor, gemini-cli, openclaw, pi-cli, vscode, windsurf

Options:
      --scope <SCOPE>   Scope: project (default for most tools) or user
      --with-mcp        Also register tirith MCP server (Claude Code and Gemini CLI)
      --install-zshenv  Append zshenv guard to ~/.zshenv (default: print snippet only)
      --dry-run         Show what would be written without writing
      --force           Overwrite existing files and update stale entries
      --update-configs  Refresh embedded hook scripts and gateway config to latest defaults. WARNING: overwrites local edits to generated hook scripts and gateway.yaml. Does not re-register MCP servers or modify shell profiles — use full setup for that
  -h, --help            Print help

Examples:
  tirith setup claude-code --with-mcp
  tirith setup cursor
  tirith setup claude-code --dry-run
